data.title: Classification of Voice
data.meta_description: Classification of Voice - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document discusses the classification of voices and genres of music. It describes the main categories that voices are divided into, such as soprano, mezzo-soprano, contralto, tenor, baritone and bass. It also discusses vocal ranges and subcategories within each category. The document then provides examples of the main genres of music, such as pop, rock, jazz, dubstep, rhythm and blues, techno, country, electro, indie rock, rap and reggae. It concludes by stating that pop music is still the most commonly heard genre worldwide, while the number of genres continues to grow with new hybrid styles emerging.
